      "text": [
        " رَجُلَيْنِ اِخْتَصَمَا إِلَيْهِ فِي خُصٍّ فَقَالَ \"إِنَّ اَلْخُصَّ لِلَّذِي إِلَيْهِ اَلْقُمُطُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3413 - Amr ibn Shimr narrated from Jabir, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), from his father, from his grandfather, from Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as):\nHe ruled in a case where two men disputed over a reed fence (khuss).\nImam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said: \"The fence belongs to the one to whom the boundary rope (al-qimat) is attached.\""
        ]
      }
    },
